House Resolution 550
By: Representative Powell of the 33rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Kenneth Wayne Brown; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Kenneth Wayne Brown on February 8, 2025; and
4 WHEREAS, Kenneth Wayne Brown was born on June 30, 1934, in Hartwell, Georgia, a
5 beloved son of Joe and Lorene Herring Brown; and
6 WHEREAS, he served as a guardian of this nation's freedom and liberty with the United
7 States Army, valiantly and courageously protecting his fellow Americans during the Korean
8 War; and
9 WHEREAS, Kenneth Wayne Brown retired from the Hart County School System, working
10 in the maintenance department; and
11 WHEREAS, he was a bus driver, employed at Monroe Auto Equipment Company, and
12 served on the Hart County Board of Commissioners for 14 years; and
