13 WHEREAS, a man of deep and abiding faith, Kenneth Wayne Brown was an active member
14 of Rock Springs Baptist Church; and
15 WHEREAS, he was united in love and marriage to his wife, Betty, and was blessed with two
16 remarkable children, Mike and Tim, two wonderful grandchildren, Jennifer and Betsy, and
17 two great grandchildren, Cane and Chase; and
18 WHEREAS, Kenneth Wayne Brown loved his family, church, cars and tractors, and will be
19 remembered as a great hay farmer; and
20 WHEREAS, he gave inspiration to many through his high ideals, morals, and deep concern
21 for his fellow citizens, and the devotion, patience, and understanding he demonstrated to his
22 family and friends were admired by others; and
23 WHEREAS, he was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
24 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example he made of his life, he
25 made this world a better place in which to live; and
26 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous man, Kenneth Wayne Brown will long be
27 remembered for his love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who
28 had the great fortune of knowing him.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Kenneth Wayne Brown
31 and express their deepest and most sincere regret at his passing.
